    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1916-11-11T11:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1916-11-11T11:00:00-05:00" n="1136"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1136">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 763.72115/2548</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Minister in Belgium</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_WB1"
                        type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Whitlock</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Brussels</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1916-11-11T17:00:00+01:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">November 11, 1916, 5 p. m.</hi>
                        </date>
                        <lb/> [<hi rend="italic">Received November 15, 7.30 p. m.</hi>]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>15. My 14. I have just had long and interesting conversation with <persName
                        corresp="#p_LBVD">Lancken</persName> just returned from Berlin. The idea of
                    opening camps of Belgian workmen in Germany to visit and inspection of neutral
                    powers impresses him most favorably. He is wiring Berlin to urge consideration
                    and adoption. I suggest, therefore, that the idea be presented to the German
                    Government. The fact that Belgian interests in Germany are represented by Spain
                    might make it indelicate on our part to suggest that the inspection be wholly
                    under American auspices, but it could be under the joint American-Spanish
                    auspices, or possibly be regarded as extension of work of Commission Relief
                    Belgium. <persName corresp="#p_LBVD">Lancken</persName> says that he will be
                    glad to do what he can to correct injustices which I might bring to his
                    attention.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_WB1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Whitlock</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
